----------------
On steep, small slope on Easter border of Kreuzweg moor. Grass and some rocks.
Bottom of slope concave!

PROFILE
-------
Well consolidated with a few soft layers and a hard to soft, small to large grain interface with very early snow cover.
Winter started around 22 November 2015 at this location (from PAR2)

143-142: Large SH crystals (6 mm) composed of smaller crystals (2mm)
35-32: DH (DHxr) found after CT broke at tap 12.
32-0: including ice layers and melt-freeze formations

RUTSCHBLOCK
-----------
CT: Column not 30 x 30 cm at base. =&gt; probable reason for fracture.

AVATECH SP2:
- One functional measurement available from 5 at this site.
- 2 valid measurements at Versuchsfeld Weissfluhjoch the same day.

SNOW SURFACE
------------
SH

